New Zealand Survey Says 51% Expect Rugby World Cup to Be Good for Economy

-- B y   T r a c y   W i t h e r s
-- 
2011-08-02T01:10:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/new-zealand-survey-says-51-expect-rugby-world-cup-to-be-good-for-economy.html
New Zealanders expect the Rugby World
Cup in September and October will be disruptive and good for the
economy, according to a UMR Research survey of 850 people.  Forty one percent agree or strongly agree that the cup will
be very disruptive for many people, while 37 percent were
neutral, UMR said in an e-mailed statement. Fifty one percent
agree that the cup will be good for the economy, while 15
percent disagree or strongly disagree.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tracy Withers at 
 twithers@bloomberg.net  